<section class="style-guide__section">
  <div class="style-guide__separate-items">
    <button class="cta cta--high">High emphasis CTA</button>
    <button class="cta cta--high cta--right-icon">High emphasis CTA {{icon('arrow-forward')}}</button>
    <button class="cta cta--high cta--left-icon">{{icon('arrow-back')}} High emphasis CTA</button>
  </div>
  <div class="type">
    <p>High-emphasis CTAs are used for calls to action that need to stand out against its surroundings, or for the primary action when multiple calls to action are present. They can be styled by including both the <code>cta</code> and <code>cta--high</code> classes.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="style-guide__section">
  <div class="style-guide__separate-items">
    <button class="cta cta--medium">Medium emphasis CTA</button>
    <button class="cta cta--medium cta--right-icon">Medium emphasis CTA {{icon('arrow-forward')}}</button>
    <button class="cta cta--medium cta--left-icon">{{icon('arrow-back')}} Medium emphasis CTA</button>
  </div>
  <div class="type">
    <p>Medium-emphasis CTAs are used for calls to action that do not take precedence in a given situation, for instance as a secondary action when multiple calls to action are present. They can be styled by including both the <code>cta</code> and <code>cta--medium</code> classes.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="style-guide__section">
  <div class="style-guide__separate-items">
    <button class="cta cta--low cta--right-icon">Low emphasis CTA Link {{icon('arrow-forward')}}</button>
    <button class="cta cta--low cta--left-icon">{{icon('arrow-back')}} Low emphasis CTA</button>
  </div>
  <div class="type">
    <p>Low-emphasis CTAs are used when the call to action is not meant to stand out but rather be a smaller part of a larger component, for instance on cards. Low-emphasis CTAs <em>must always</em> include an icon to distinguish it as clickable. They can be styled by including bot the <code>cta</code> and <code>cta--low</code> classes.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="style-guide__section">
  <div class="style-guide__separate-items">
    <a href="/en" class="cta cta--link">Internal Link</a>
    <a href="https://google.com" class="cta cta--link">External Link</a>
    <a href="https://google.com" class="cta cta--back">Back Link</a>
  </div>
  <div class="type">
    <p>A very common use of the low-emphasis CTA across components is as like that points to either an internal or external URL, or as a back indicator. As a convenience, they can be styled by including both the <code>cta</code> and either the <code>cta--link</code> or <code>cta--back</code> classes (respectively), which will consistently handle these use cases, complete with internal vs external arrow indicator.</p>
  </div>
</section>
